==English==
===Alternative spellings===
* [[Google whore]], [[GoogleWhore]], [[Google-Whore]]

===Verb===
'''googlewhore'''
# ''(Internet slang)'' To promote via [[Google]]; in particular, to do so by [[googlebomb]]ing.

====Derived terms====
* [[googlewhoring]]

====Quotations====
* '''January 2004,''' comment in ''Meta-Roj Blog'' [http://www.rojisan.com/blog/2004/01/reformed_blogspammer_id_credit_factor.html]
*: For the most part, it seems as if people who are submitting trackback spam are doing it to karma whore on google. ('''GoogleWhore'''?)
* '''November 2004,''' Alex, ''Catechism,'' [http://pedagogism.blogspot.com/2004/11/on-elders-and-pageviews.html]
*: In this way, we measure our relative success, track key words, '''googlewhore''' ourselves and note which blogs are linking to us, who's following the links and how many people are coming from where.

===Noun===
'''googlewhore'''
# ''(Internet slang)'' An ardent user of Google services.
# ''(Internet slang)'' One who [[googlebomb]]s.


